race.comment: SPURLINE (3) was quickly back on track last time out when she worked home well to finish just 1L over 1460m at this track. Best figures measure up and she's won 2/2 this track/trip. Has the inside barrier and is sure to run well. HURRICANE CONI (1) also lines up for a local stable and has gone close at Goulburn his last two over this trip. He can race forward and Cahill is a positive jockey booking. Well placed and will be right in it. TILLMAN (4) spiked his figures winning at Cootamundra and then was on speed beaten 1.7Lover 1460m at this track. Has a wide gate but can make the finish with average luck. POKER FLASH (5) wasn't beaten too far over this trip at Canberra in a bit stronger and was a comfortable Maiden win there prior. Gets in well with the 2kg claim and has each-way claims.
